The way the text wraps around just looks yucky to me. Thankfully thereâ€™s a solution! Make it possible for your code blocks to scroll from side to side by adding the following to your CSS:

pre code {
  overflow: auto;
  word-wrap: normal;
  white-space: pre;
}

Then gaze upon the resulting beauty:

If you want to add this feature to a simple R Markdown document, you can put the code above in a file called styles.css, then you can use it in your document with the following yaml front matter:

---
output: 
  html_document:
    css: styles.css
---

Your mobile readers will thank you! If you want to see how this was implemented on a real blog check out this pull request.
